description:
&lt;p&gt;Minehead Community Hospital is looking to recruit enthusiastic generic assistants to join the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role involves a variety of tasks across all the Hotel Services departments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have a key role in all areas including portering and catering along side housekeeping within the hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A good eye for the cleanliness and high standards help reduce the risk of infection and that supports towards patient care while they are in hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to work as part of a team and be flexible within your approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The working hours will be between 0700 - 1900 and includes some evenings and weekends to meet the needs of the services.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essentially you will be a team player who is committed to ensuring that the Hotel Services department delivers the highest level of services to improve patient experience by providing a safe and clean environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge and experience is preferred but full training will be given.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we provide above basic rates of pay, weekend enhancements, generous holiday entitlements and a pension scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;P&lt;strong&gt;revious applicants need not apply&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Julie Lindley&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hotel Services Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Julie.lindley@somersetft.nhs.uk / 01643 701742&lt;/p&gt;
